Mahogany seeds are seeds used in the Farming skill. At level 55 Farming, mahogany seeds may be planted in plant pots with a trowel and watered to become mahogany saplings.

After planting the sapling in a hardwood tree patch found in Fossil Island and waiting for it to fully grow, which takes 5,120 minutes (8x640 minutes or 85.3 hours), the plant will grow into a mahogany tree which can be cut to yield mahogany logs (and grant Woodcutting experience). Planting the mahogany sapling yields 63 experience, and checking the health yields 15,720 experience.

When cut down, the tree will automatically regrow after a period of time. The gardener will look after a mahogany tree in exchange for 25 Yanillian hops.

After planting the sapling in a [[hardwood tree patch]] found in [[Fossil Island]] and waiting for it to fully grow, which takes 5,120 minutes (8x640 minutes or 85.3 hours), the plant will grow into a [[mahogany]] tree which can be cut to yield [[mahogany logs]] (and grant [[Woodcutting]] [[experience]]). Planting the mahogany sapling yields 63 experience, and checking the health yields 15,720 experience.

When cut down, the tree will automatically regrow after a period of time. The gardener will look after a mahogany tree in exchange for 25 [[Yanillian hops]].
